  "response_text": "A blurred bowling alley appears first, with people in the background and large centered text over it. The visible graphic reads “FANDUEL SPORTSBOOK” with a blue shield logo, and below it, “MORE WAYS TO WIN,” with small fine print along the bottom.\n\nThe scene then shifts to a grand, museum-like hall with high arched windows, warm hanging lights, display cases, and polished floors. Two men walk side by side down the center aisle. One is an older bald man with glasses, wearing a dark suit, white shirt, and tie; the other is a younger Black man with a short beard, wearing a dark red sweater and jeans. They appear to be touring the space together. Nearby displays include unusual damaged objects, including a large cream-colored vehicle seat mounted on a pedestal to the right.\n\nThe story moves into a car parked near a scenic coastline. Inside the front seats are a couple, both wearing seatbelts. The woman in the passenger seat has straight dark hair and wears a light top with a green scarf or sweater layer. The man driving has short dark hair with some gray and wears a reddish-brown sweater. They look relaxed and affectionate. Outside, the car sits by a rocky ocean overlook, with waves breaking against the shore and hills stretching into the distance.\n\nFrom the back seat, the couple turn toward each other in the front seats. They lean closer, smiling, as if about to kiss. Above them is a large glass sunroof. Suddenly, foamy seawater crashes down through the roof area. The interior fills with rushing water and spray, obscuring the couple. Their arms and hands flail through the foam as the water surges around them.\n\nThe car’s cabin becomes half-submerged from the inside, with water sloshing up to chest height. The woman raises both hands near her head, startled and drenched. The man, still at the steering wheel, looks alarmed and reaches toward her as water pours over the dashboard and seats. The windows and windshield are streaked with water, and the entire interior looks like an aquarium.\n\nUnder the waterline, a pinkish-red tentacle appears, snaking through the flooded cabin near the dashboard and front seats. Back inside, the couple stare at it in shock as it rises between them, curling upward from the water. The man turns toward the woman, open-mouthed, while she holds a hand near her face and watches the tentacle warily. The water continues to churn around the pale gray seats.\n\nThe tentacle moves underwater again, sliding along the front of the cabin. Outside the car, water suddenly gushes from an open rear door onto the wet pavement beside the ocean overlook. The silver sedan sits with its door wide open, water pouring out in a frothy stream. A red tentacle-like shape spills or wriggles out with the water onto the ground.\n\nThe scene returns to the museum hall. The older suited man and the younger man stand beside the large cream-colored car seat display. The older man faces forward as if explaining the exhibit, while the younger man looks at him. Small legal text appears along the bottom of the screen. A closer view of the display shows the cream car seat mounted upright on a dark, wet-looking pile of debris, with sea-themed objects or tangled material on and around it, suggesting the strange flooded-car incident has been preserved as a claim exhibit.\n\nThe two men continue standing in the hall with the damaged seat display at their side. Finally, the screen turns white with the Farmers Insurance logo centered: a blue and red shield-like emblem above the word “FARMERS” in large blue letters, with “INSURANCE” in smaller red letters beneath.",
